cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a novel method for multi-object tracking using deep learning techniques such as CNN and RNN. The focus is on processing tracklets to handle crowd and long-term occlusion scenarios. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of deep learning models for processing tracklets, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The application of the proposed method is in surveillance and autonomous driving, which falls under robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of datasets for training and evaluation, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) category.
